Sequence Information.Source: Gallus gallus, a 25-residue fragment from chicken breast obtained via enzyme digestion and isolation

Literature.Author: Maky MA, Zendo T. 2023
Literature.Title: Identification of a Novel Bioactive Peptide Derived from Frozen Chicken Breast Hydrolysate and the Utilization of Hydrolysates as Biopreservatives

Sequence Information.Comments: Discovery: a natural fragment isolated from enzyme digestion of beef.Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (34.62%) toBombolitin IV.Activity: Active against E-faecalis JCM 5803T (MIC >24ug/ml), L-innocua ATCC 33090T (MIC >24 ug/ml), E. coli JM109 (MIC 24 ug/ml), B-coagulans CM 2257 (MIC >24 ug/ml), P-putida ATCC 12633 (MIC >24 ug/ml), S-enterica subsp. enterica NBRC 13245 (MIC >24 ug/ml), and P. vulgaris F24B (MIC 24 ug/ml).
